      "authors": "Alkalaev, Konstantin, Mandrygin, Semyon",
      "description": "Parametric one-loop four-point conformal integral in $D$ dimensions with arbitrary propagator powers $a_1,a_2,a_3,a_4$ obeying $a_1+a_2+a_3+a_4=D$ (conformality condition). Defined in position space as $I_4^{a}(x) = \\int d^D x_0 / \\pi^{D/2} \\prod_{i=1}^{4} X_{0i}^{-a_i}$ with $X_{ij}=(x_i-x_j)^2$ (Eq. 2.1). Evaluated in closed form via the bipartite Mellin-Barnes representation as a $Z_4$-invariant sum of four Appell $F_4$ basis functions generated by cyclic permutations from a single master function (Eqs. 5.17-5.18). Cross-ratios $u=X_{12} X_{34}/(X_{13} X_{24})$, $v=X_{14} X_{23}/(X_{13} X_{24})$. Non-parametric limit $a_i=1$, $D=4$ reproduces the Bloch-Wigner / Davydychev form in terms of the Bloch-Wigner function $\\Phi(z,y)$.",
