      "authors": "He, Song, Li, Zhenjie, Zhang, Chi",
      "description": "One-loop four-mass box integral I_{a,b,c,d} of dual-conformal-invariant N=4 SYM amplitudes. In dual coordinates the integrand reads -x_{ac}^2 x_{bd}^2 Delta / (x_{0a}^2 x_{0b}^2 x_{0c}^2 x_{0d}^2). UV/IR finite because all four corners are massive (each corner is a cluster of two or more external null momenta of the parent amplitude). Closed-form evaluation in eq. (3.4): I = -Li_2(z) + Li_2(zbar) - (1/2) log(z*zbar) log((1-z)/(1-zbar)), with z, zbar defined through the cross-ratios u = p1^2*p3^2/(s*t), v = p2^2*p4^2/(s*t) and Delta = sqrt((1-u-v)^2 - 4*u*v). This box is the carrier of the algebraic letters Delta_{a,b,c,d} that show up in the symbol of two-loop NMHV n-point amplitudes via the Q-bar equation.",
